20/10/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkish border police on Saturday (18 October) discovered 141kg of heroin on a Romanian bus, which was entering the country at Kapikule, on the Bulgarian border.
Hundreds of small plastic bags full of drugs were discovered in the coach's air conditioning system and fuel tank.
The street value of the heroin was assessed at more than 10m euros.
(AFP - 19/10/03, 18/10/03)
